[[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]SCP-8822-1, '-2 and '-4 were recovered from The Salford Masonry in Salford (near Manchester, England). SCP-8822-3 was recovered from the womens' bathroom of the Stone Head Delicatessen in the Salford Quays area, where it had been on display for several years.[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]SCP-8822 were recovered from a shopfront in Salford (near Manchester, England), which was formerly the site of The Salford Masonry, a commercial sculptor's workshop that went out of business in 2009.[[/span]][[/span]]

In a series of anonymous posts on the [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]][[[the-bathrooms-wiki | Bathrooms Wiki]]][[/span]][[span class="a_10"]][[[https://parawatch.net | Parawatch Wiki]]][[/span]][[/span]] between [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]2015[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]2021[[/span]][[/span]] and 2023, [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]eight[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]two[[/span]][[/span]] users local to the [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Bradford[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Salford[[/span]][[/span]] area described illegally breaking into The [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Bradford[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Salford[[/span]][[/span]] Masonry on separate [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]occasions after having seen SCP-8822-3. All[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]occasions. Both[[/span]][[/span]] users allegedly experienced mind-altering effects inside the building, reporting discrepancies between their recollection, photographs taken, and even previous drafts of their posts.

The Foundation acquired [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]The Salford Masonry[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]the building[[/span]][[/span]] from the [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Bradford[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Salford[[/span]][[/span]] City Council [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]but, as an active business, was unable to acquire the Stone Head Delicatessen.[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]on 2023-05-13.[[/span]][[/span]]

On 2024-10-13, Agent Marques of Site-199 visited the Masonry to verify the claims made on the [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]Bathrooms[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Parawatch[[/span]][[/span]] Wiki. Marques was able to corroborate many of them, but could not prove any; additionally, he described feeling at one point as if he were recovering from a compulsion effect, which would be consistent with having been compelled to forget something. Marques suggested that the [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]Masonry and the Delicatessen were the focal point of a dual-centre[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]building housed a localised[[/span]][[/span]] confusion effect, and recommended a disruption class of [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Vlam[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Dark[[/span]][[/span]] and a risk class of Notice.

On 2024-10-15, a [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]three-person[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]four-person[[/span]][[/span]] research team was deployed to [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Bradford[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Salford[[/span]][[/span]] from [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_35"]]Site-91[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Site-199[[/span]][[/span]]. The researchers investigated The [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_28"]]Bradford[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Salford[[/span]][[/span]] [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_23"]]Masonry and the Stone Head Delicatessen,[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Masonry,[[/span]][[/span]] confirmed that anomalous activity was present, and recovered the heads for containment at [[span class="ch_B"]][[span class="a_35"]]Site-91[[/span]][[span class="a_10"]]Site-199[[/span]][[/span]].

